  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Including 89 randomised patient, the studies aim is to determine whether an economisation
      and/or improvement in terms of operating time, drainage fluid, blood loss, time of
      hospitalisation can be found using an electrosurgical sealing device versus traditional
      surgical methods such as stitches an ligations.The study is performed for patients undergoing
      partial pancreatoduodenectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
